[SPEAKER_14]: Thanks, Mike.

106
00:07:11,766 --> 00:07:13,767
[SPEAKER_14]: Good evening, Chairman Caldera, members of the board.

107
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,308
[SPEAKER_14]: My name is Adam Barnosky.

108
00:07:15,328 --> 00:07:19,350
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm at the platform of Roberto Israel and Weiner, 255 State Street in Boston.

109
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:24,273
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm here on behalf of Anteleto Brothers, Inc., the property owner and proposed developer.

110
00:07:24,313 --> 00:07:27,575
[SPEAKER_14]: With me today is Joe Anteleto, the petitioner.

111
00:07:28,055 --> 00:07:32,259
[SPEAKER_14]: Peter Quinn, the project architect, and my co-counsel, Michael Barone.

112
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:41,927
[SPEAKER_14]: As the board might recall, I recognize that this project has been going on for a while, and there are some members of the board that may be more familiar with it than others.

113
00:07:42,988 --> 00:07:51,416
[SPEAKER_14]: But this project involves a proposed mixed-use five-story building on the southeasterly corner of Boston Avenue and Harvard Street at 590 Boston Ave.

114
00:07:52,096 --> 00:08:01,893
[SPEAKER_14]: The applicant in this project previously appeared before this board in 2020 and then in 2021 and obtained relief including use of dimensional variances in case number A2020-7.

115
00:08:04,218 --> 00:08:21,845
[SPEAKER_14]: We are here this evening, as Dennis mentioned, to request modifications to the project, which are based in part on recent revisions to the zoning code, as well as updates that align the project more with the economic conditions which have occurred since the original approvals.

116
00:08:22,808 --> 00:08:35,894
[SPEAKER_14]: As I'll detail in a moment, with the exception of two setback modifications, the requested revisions reduce the noncompliance, increase existing compliance, or negate the need for the previously granted approvals.

117
00:08:36,595 --> 00:08:42,877
[SPEAKER_14]: The updated project, as revised, received unanimous approval of the Community Development Board at its October 4th meeting.

118
00:08:43,518 --> 00:08:45,499
[SPEAKER_14]: So first, a quick background on the property.

119
00:08:45,559 --> 00:08:50,261
[SPEAKER_14]: It currently operates as a gas and car wash on the corner of Boston Avenue and Harvard Street.

120
00:08:50,861 --> 00:08:55,383
[SPEAKER_14]: It is owned and operated by Joe Anoletto and has been run by his family for over 60 years.

121
00:08:56,783 --> 00:09:05,526
[SPEAKER_14]: The premises is situated on a rectangular lot in the industrial zoning district just north of GLX Ball Square station and across the street from Tufts.

122
00:09:06,287 --> 00:09:15,210
[SPEAKER_14]: It is subject to an easement for the benefit of the MBTA along the GLX line and another easement for the benefit of Medford along Harvard Street.

123
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:20,832
[SPEAKER_14]: The architect, we're going to have Peter run through the plans in a moment.

124
00:09:21,112 --> 00:09:25,173
[SPEAKER_14]: But first, I just wanted to talk about the notable practical changes to the project.

125
00:09:25,733 --> 00:09:31,675
[SPEAKER_14]: We did include a table relative to these changes that the board can look at.

126
00:09:32,455 --> 00:09:36,376
[SPEAKER_14]: But overall, we are going to be decreasing the total gross floor area to 41,306.

127
00:09:36,416 --> 00:09:38,697
[SPEAKER_14]: That's a net decrease of about 5,000 square feet.

128
00:09:41,478 --> 00:09:47,600
[SPEAKER_14]: There will be a reduced lot coverage to 41.5%, which is a reduction of 5.5%.

129
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:50,681
[SPEAKER_14]: Reduced height, we're going down three feet.

130
00:09:50,801 --> 00:09:54,462
[SPEAKER_14]: The new proposed buildings will be 58.4 feet.

131
00:09:55,083 --> 00:09:57,884
[SPEAKER_14]: There will be an increase to the retail space.

132
00:09:57,944 --> 00:10:00,404
[SPEAKER_14]: Although it's de minimis, we're adding an additional 121 square feet there.

133
00:10:02,865 --> 00:10:06,046
[SPEAKER_14]: increase residential units from 40 to 45.

134
00:10:06,166 --> 00:10:07,627
[SPEAKER_14]: That's an increase of five.

135
00:10:08,187 --> 00:10:10,768
[SPEAKER_14]: There will be a second residential amenity space.

136
00:10:11,628 --> 00:10:14,949
[SPEAKER_14]: We are reducing the parking to 34 spaces.

137
00:10:15,009 --> 00:10:19,691
[SPEAKER_14]: This is a net reduction of six, but it is now still compliant with the new ordinances.

138
00:10:20,951 --> 00:10:22,832
[SPEAKER_14]: There will be an increase to bike spaces to 46.

139
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:28,565
[SPEAKER_14]: and of particular note is that parking is now at grade.

140
00:10:29,246 --> 00:10:31,067
[SPEAKER_14]: Parking was previously below grade.

141
00:10:31,928 --> 00:10:43,476
[SPEAKER_14]: This allowed for the removal of a retaining wall on the southeasterly lot line, and it allows for a reconfiguration of the entrance aisle.

142
00:10:43,876 --> 00:10:48,760
[SPEAKER_14]: There is a 25-foot wide curb cut, and it now permits two-way traffic.

143
00:10:50,363 --> 00:11:00,228
[SPEAKER_14]: So, as I mentioned, this is mostly going to decrease noncompliance, increase compliance, and negate the requirement for some relief.

144
00:11:00,288 --> 00:11:06,552
[SPEAKER_14]: There are two facets that require new relief from this board, which is what I'm assuming would be of most interest.

145
00:11:06,752 --> 00:11:14,357
[SPEAKER_14]: One is the side yard, which was requested in 2019, but it was omitted from the board's decision.

146
00:11:15,037 --> 00:11:17,758
[SPEAKER_14]: It was granted by the board, but again, it wasn't in the written decision.

147
00:11:17,838 --> 00:11:22,979
[SPEAKER_14]: So now there is actually a reduction in the scope of that side yard variance.

148
00:11:23,079 --> 00:11:26,939
[SPEAKER_14]: We only need a 1.2 foot variance in the side yard.

149
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:31,440
[SPEAKER_14]: And the second is the parking setback, which was compliant in 2019.

150
00:11:32,901 --> 00:11:35,821
[SPEAKER_14]: It was compliant where 14 feet were required.

151
00:11:35,841 --> 00:11:38,722
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm sorry, it was 14 feet where six were required.

152
00:11:39,442 --> 00:11:41,442
[SPEAKER_14]: And now we do need a six foot variance.

153
00:11:41,462 --> 00:11:44,263
[SPEAKER_14]: So we can look at the plans and we can run through that in a moment.

154
00:11:44,863 --> 00:11:46,064
[SPEAKER_14]: that we're going to have to deal with.

155
00:11:46,084 --> 00:12:00,556
[SPEAKER_14]: So with that, I'll provide some to the extent the board would like to rehear some of the elements on the legal end for why this relief is both needed and complies with the requirements for variance.

156
00:12:00,596 --> 00:12:01,477
[SPEAKER_14]: I can get to that in a moment.

157
00:12:01,757 --> 00:12:05,460
[SPEAKER_14]: For now, I would like to pass it along to Peter Quinn to run

158
00:12:14,017 --> 00:12:20,459
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah, for the record, my name is Peter Quinn of Peter Quinn Architects in 259 Elm Street, Somerville.

159
00:12:22,079 --> 00:12:25,620
[SPEAKER_16]: If I could share my screen, I'll take you through the drawings quickly.

160
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,481
[SPEAKER_16]: Okay, looks like I can do that.

161
00:12:29,501 --> 00:12:30,821
[SPEAKER_16]: Here we go.

162
00:12:32,821 --> 00:12:35,662
[SPEAKER_16]: If somebody could just say when they can see it, then I'm good to go.

163
00:12:36,884 --> 00:12:37,985
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes, we can see it.

164
00:12:38,345 --> 00:12:38,546
[SPEAKER_16]: Great.

165
00:12:38,726 --> 00:12:39,046
[SPEAKER_16]: Thank you.

166
00:12:40,067 --> 00:12:50,757
[SPEAKER_16]: So as you can see in this plan here, if you look at it briefly, we have basically a wraparound driveway with parking spaces arranged like piano keys off of that.

167
00:12:52,058 --> 00:12:59,364
[SPEAKER_16]: In the previous scheme, we actually had turned this side into a ramp, and then you went into an underground basement.

168
00:12:59,464 --> 00:13:02,247
[SPEAKER_16]: And of course, that was a huge cost.

169
00:13:03,755 --> 00:13:15,058
[SPEAKER_16]: In addition to that, we ran into some technical problems with the water table on the site that made it prohibitively expensive to do.

170
00:13:16,038 --> 00:13:25,001
[SPEAKER_16]: So coincidentally, the city had changed its regulations on parking, which opened up this possibility of having on-way parking as we are now proposing.

171
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:42,374
[SPEAKER_16]: basically this is a building without a basement and it is built in such a way that all the utilities and everything is on the ground floor and we have a retail space at the corner as we did originally.

172
00:13:42,414 --> 00:13:44,456
[SPEAKER_16]: It's approximately the same size as before.

173
00:13:45,237 --> 00:13:48,419
[SPEAKER_16]: We have living rooms and the like and mail rooms for the

174
00:13:49,963 --> 00:13:58,366
[SPEAKER_16]: for the residents, a bike room that's all sheltered, as mentioned, and a nice unit on the ground floor with its own outdoor patio.

175
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:06,409
[SPEAKER_16]: We've been able to increase the amount of landscape in the front by not having elevated plinths that had the garage underneath it.

176
00:14:08,109 --> 00:14:12,471
[SPEAKER_16]: So we're able to get more robust plantings in the front as well.

177
00:14:13,471 --> 00:14:16,272
[SPEAKER_16]: Just to give you an idea of what this looks like,

178
00:14:17,226 --> 00:14:22,267
[SPEAKER_16]: This was, this is the rear view, and I show that comparison to what we had before.

179
00:14:22,287 --> 00:14:32,550
[SPEAKER_16]: You can see here, before we were down below the building in quite a complex technical, with a T right next to it.

180
00:14:33,430 --> 00:14:40,112
[SPEAKER_16]: And now it's primarily, it's all above, all at grade, essentially.

181
00:14:41,653 --> 00:14:42,513
[SPEAKER_16]: In the front of the building,

182
00:14:43,868 --> 00:14:46,009
[SPEAKER_16]: This was the proposed view.

183
00:14:46,109 --> 00:14:58,013
[SPEAKER_16]: I think I could say that we made this facade a little more interesting with a nice brick base, and then balconies and the like arranged in the pattern on the building.

184
00:14:58,573 --> 00:15:04,556
[SPEAKER_16]: The previous design was a little more random.

185
00:15:05,216 --> 00:15:13,479
