218
00:19:00,883 --> 00:19:10,711
[SPEAKER_03]: this time, because that will help us then as a board to assess if the elements of the project that changed somehow changed that analysis in any way.

219
00:19:11,532 --> 00:19:17,918
[SPEAKER_03]: So before we get into full-fledged questions, I don't want to treat this like we would a brand new case.

220
00:19:18,458 --> 00:19:22,101
[SPEAKER_03]: I think that would just be helpful context for some of our newer members of the board.

221
00:19:22,121 --> 00:19:24,664
[SPEAKER_03]: Does that work for you, Attorney Bernowski?

222
00:19:25,244 --> 00:19:25,885
[SPEAKER_14]: Yes, thank you.

223
00:19:26,842 --> 00:19:38,488
[SPEAKER_14]: Yes, so as I mentioned before, the board previously found that the project met the required statutory criteria for both dimensional and use variances under 40A section 10.

224
00:19:39,649 --> 00:19:45,392
[SPEAKER_14]: So those, the reasons and all the elements under 40A section 10 are

225
00:19:47,713 --> 00:20:04,080
[SPEAKER_14]: uh provided for in in great detail in that decision but in uh in summary we talked a lot about you know this first prong relating to soil condition shape or topography this is a unique uh it's a unique parcel within the industrial zoning district

226
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,982
[SPEAKER_14]: It is subject to several municipal and public agency easements.

227
00:20:08,462 --> 00:20:17,248
[SPEAKER_14]: It's bound by public roads on two sides, Boston Avenue, Harvard Street, and then the MBTA commuter line rail.

228
00:20:17,388 --> 00:20:22,471
[SPEAKER_14]: And then in addition to the easements, it creates a difficult lot to build on.

229
00:20:22,951 --> 00:20:26,535
[SPEAKER_14]: The easements restrict the layout and the placement of the proposed buildings and parking.

230
00:20:26,555 --> 00:20:31,599
[SPEAKER_14]: And what it essentially does is kind of requires everything to build up as opposed to out.

231
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:38,025
[SPEAKER_14]: So to be in compliance really would be challenging.

232
00:20:38,125 --> 00:20:45,953
[SPEAKER_14]: And that was a big part of the discussion we had back in 2020 and 21 relative to the setbacks and what could really be built on there.

233
00:20:47,874 --> 00:21:03,459
[SPEAKER_14]: I think at the time we said it would be very difficult to build anything functionally that would comply with all the setbacks and also be in compliance with the easements and not interfere with some of the more challenging aspects of the site.

234
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:06,743
[SPEAKER_14]: So this is unique to the zoning district.

235
00:21:06,763 --> 00:21:17,580
[SPEAKER_14]: There's no other lots that we were able to establish in the zoning district that face this configuration and that the literal enforcement of the ordinance would involve substantial hardship.

236
00:21:19,366 --> 00:21:26,051
[SPEAKER_14]: Again, the railroad corridor and easements intensify the setback issues and they further constrain the possible layout of any development property.

237
00:21:27,132 --> 00:21:43,626
[SPEAKER_14]: The surrounding neighborhood has transformed from industrial to the mix of residential commercial uses along the industrial corridor and enforcement of the industrial zoning district use would prohibit a development just like this.

238
00:21:44,126 --> 00:21:45,968
[SPEAKER_14]: And that was a huge discussion we had

239
00:21:46,495 --> 00:21:48,958
[SPEAKER_14]: relative to the use variance in 2020 and 2021.

240
00:21:49,738 --> 00:21:56,626
[SPEAKER_14]: Now, the use here is not changing, so I wouldn't anticipate that that component would be a piece of the board's decision today.

241
00:21:57,767 --> 00:22:07,036
[SPEAKER_14]: And finally, that relief could be granted without substantial detriment to the public good or nullification or substantial derogation to the ordinance because this is an existing project.

242
00:22:08,017 --> 00:22:10,198
[SPEAKER_14]: and where it's already met these threshold requirements.

243
00:22:10,218 --> 00:22:17,302
[SPEAKER_14]: We don't think that what we're seeking now is going to derogate from the intent of the bylaw or of the 2021 decision.

244
00:22:18,443 --> 00:22:24,266
[SPEAKER_14]: The requested modifications in many ways are in greater compliance than the original relief that was granted.

245
00:22:24,907 --> 00:22:30,850
[SPEAKER_14]: And this, again, does come before the board with the unanimous support of the Community Development Board.

246
00:22:32,103 --> 00:22:34,765
[SPEAKER_14]: So that's essentially where we're looking at the legal argument.

247
00:22:34,785 --> 00:22:39,769
[SPEAKER_14]: We're happy to answer any questions the board may have or dig into any of those components in more detail.

248
00:22:41,450 --> 00:22:42,851
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you, Attorney Bernanke.

249
00:22:42,871 --> 00:22:51,939
