[SPEAKER_03]: Mike?

396
00:37:57,580 --> 00:37:57,680
[SPEAKER_03]: Aye.

397
00:37:59,144 --> 00:38:01,247
[SPEAKER_03]: Right, so the public portion of the hearing is now closed.

398
00:38:01,267 --> 00:38:02,249
[SPEAKER_03]: We are now deliberating.

399
00:38:04,412 --> 00:38:05,213
[SPEAKER_03]: What do you think, folks?

400
00:38:08,217 --> 00:38:15,228
[SPEAKER_03]: And by the way, I think I could just say it up front, but Mary, you are voting on this matter, so we haven't heard any testimony before today.

401
00:38:22,303 --> 00:38:37,979
[SPEAKER_06]: I think that if it's just a modification of something that's been approved and what they are requesting is less than what was required.

402
00:38:37,999 --> 00:38:40,681
[SPEAKER_06]: Am I correct?

403
00:38:40,761 --> 00:38:42,163
[SPEAKER_06]: That was my understanding of this.

404
00:38:42,985 --> 00:38:44,005
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, that's right, Mary.

405
00:38:45,166 --> 00:38:49,388
[SPEAKER_03]: So this was approved back in 2020, as I understand it.

406
00:38:50,248 --> 00:38:55,531
[SPEAKER_03]: And the zoning has changed between then and now.

407
00:38:57,051 --> 00:39:10,237
[SPEAKER_03]: But the net effect of this request is that most of the granted variances decrease, dimensional variances,

408
00:39:12,222 --> 00:39:16,964
[SPEAKER_03]: decreased in magnitude relative to what was already approved.

409
00:39:18,525 --> 00:39:33,952
[SPEAKER_03]: It appears that there was one variance that was discussed at the time, but that was just not in the decision surrounding parking setbacks, which is considered new, but it has lessened as well.

410
00:39:35,693 --> 00:39:40,876
[SPEAKER_03]: And then the five dwelling units have been added

411
00:39:41,987 --> 00:39:43,249
[SPEAKER_03]: As part of this redesign.

412
00:39:43,269 --> 00:39:46,653
[SPEAKER_03]: And so the lot area per dwelling unit.

413
00:39:47,454 --> 00:39:51,338
[SPEAKER_03]: Variance that was granted has intensified so.

414
00:39:51,979 --> 00:39:56,645
[SPEAKER_03]: So, technically, no, it has not all decreased, but I think in most.

415
00:39:57,446 --> 00:40:00,249
[SPEAKER_03]: Dimensions it has, so it's really just the.

416
00:40:02,151 --> 00:40:13,798
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, I wasn't on the board at the time, but assuming that there's just an error of omission on the parking setbacks, everything got more conforming except for the lot area per dwelling unit.

417
00:40:15,639 --> 00:40:16,340
[SPEAKER_17]: Okay, thank you.

418
00:40:17,020 --> 00:40:21,843
[SPEAKER_17]: Just want to clarify, I think the parking setbacks are new.

419
00:40:21,863 --> 00:40:30,188
[SPEAKER_17]: The variance that changed was the side setback with the change in the driveway.

420
00:40:31,147 --> 00:40:32,368
[SPEAKER_17]: with the retaining wall removal.

421
00:40:34,649 --> 00:40:39,772
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay, so I just want to double check that so that the board has it straight.

422
00:40:39,812 --> 00:40:45,795
[SPEAKER_03]: So the parking setbacks are new or was that just omitted?

423
00:40:45,815 --> 00:40:51,278
[SPEAKER_17]: The parking setbacks are new because of the placement of the parking spaces with regards to the building.

424
00:40:53,879 --> 00:40:58,262
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay, yeah, we have Danielle Evans from the planning department.

425
00:40:58,282 --> 00:40:58,782
[SPEAKER_03]: Please go ahead.

426
00:40:59,970 --> 00:41:03,472
[SPEAKER_01]: Good evening, Danielle Evans, senior planner through the chair.

427
00:41:04,433 --> 00:41:17,922
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes, my understanding is that the switch in the parking configuration from being subterranean to surface triggered a setback from the building that wasn't applicable before.

428
00:41:18,662 --> 00:41:19,863
[SPEAKER_01]: So that was a new one.

429
00:41:20,183 --> 00:41:23,606
[SPEAKER_01]: And then the right side setback

430
00:41:25,346 --> 00:41:38,651
[SPEAKER_01]: For whatever reason, I also was not privy to the previous decision and why that was omitted from the decision, but they want that right side setback reaffirmed.

431
00:41:40,752 --> 00:41:44,073
[SPEAKER_01]: And then it was the intensifying of the lot area per dwelling unit.

432
00:41:44,813 --> 00:41:54,617
[SPEAKER_01]: And regarding the, since it hasn't been settled whether there'll be an easement or a land donation, I would recommend that perhaps

433
00:41:56,551 --> 00:42:05,234
[SPEAKER_01]: The variance for that may be increased slightly to accommodate that, I think it was 50 square feet.

434
00:42:05,994 --> 00:42:17,217
[SPEAKER_01]: I didn't analyze whether it would cause problems with setbacks, but as far as the lot of airbird dwelling unit, that would further bring it into noncompliance.

435
00:42:17,778 --> 00:42:25,500
[SPEAKER_01]: So your decision could reflect that as a possibility, so they don't have to come back for that, but I leave that up to you all.

436
00:42:28,705 --> 00:42:32,126
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, thank you, Ms.

437
00:42:32,186 --> 00:42:32,426
[SPEAKER_03]: Evans.

438
00:42:32,566 --> 00:42:37,486
[SPEAKER_03]: So I'd like to check in with the applicant on that.

439
00:42:38,067 --> 00:42:44,168
[SPEAKER_03]: I don't believe we can grant a variance for more than was requested, so we would need a request to do something like that.

440
00:42:44,248 --> 00:42:49,469
[SPEAKER_03]: So is, yeah, I just appreciate thoughts.

441
00:42:51,529 --> 00:42:55,510
[SPEAKER_03]: My interpretation of the prior feedback was the applicant prefers the,

442
00:43:00,379 --> 00:43:01,502
[SPEAKER_03]: easement approach.

443
00:43:03,172 --> 00:43:08,414
[SPEAKER_03]: do we have attorney Bernowski to speak to that topic?

444
00:43:10,134 --> 00:43:12,735
[SPEAKER_14]: I can speak to that.

445
00:43:12,975 --> 00:43:22,779
[SPEAKER_14]: If we would have to, without any other discussion, if we would have to choose one today, I think the easement would make more sense to avoid the requirement to get further approvals.

446
00:43:22,839 --> 00:43:27,520
[SPEAKER_14]: But I don't think that there's any objection on the part of the applicant to gifting the land.

447
00:43:28,420 --> 00:43:32,602
[SPEAKER_14]: And if there's a way to do that and still have the project go forward without

448
00:43:33,202 --> 00:43:35,624
[SPEAKER_14]: I don't know that we can say with certainty either way.

449
00:43:57,223 --> 00:44:06,869
[SPEAKER_14]: but just know that the applicant is willing to work to be able to donate that for the benefit of the community in one way or the other, either by easement or conveyance.

450
00:44:08,430 --> 00:44:09,131
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay, thank you.

451
00:44:09,151 --> 00:44:14,114
[SPEAKER_03]: I see Director Hunt had her hand raised.

452
00:44:14,154 --> 00:44:15,235
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, Director Hunt.

453
00:44:17,623 --> 00:44:21,346
[SPEAKER_10]: So Mr. Chair, I just wanted to sort of chime in.

454
00:44:21,426 --> 00:44:40,621
[SPEAKER_10]: I think what Danielle and I had discussed with this particular variance that had not previously been requested is that if you grant that variance, if they request it and you grant it tonight, then there is an option they would be legally able, like we wouldn't have, they wouldn't have to come back to this board in order to then

455
00:44:41,962 --> 00:44:43,863
[SPEAKER_10]: gift that little piece of land.

456
00:44:44,704 --> 00:44:55,631
[SPEAKER_10]: If you don't give it tonight, then it takes it off the table because they'd have to come back and do a whole nother filing and a whole nother advertisement.

457
00:44:55,911 --> 00:45:00,494
[SPEAKER_10]: We didn't see it as saying that they had to decide tonight.

458
00:45:00,574 --> 00:45:05,137
[SPEAKER_10]: We actually thought that if they requested this additional variance and the board granted it,

459
00:45:05,737 --> 00:45:09,538
[SPEAKER_10]: then it was still on the table as an option.

460
00:45:10,478 --> 00:45:12,459
[SPEAKER_10]: It wasn't forcing anybody to do anything.

461
00:45:12,479 --> 00:45:17,941
[SPEAKER_10]: I think it's an open question whether this board could actually require a gift of land.

462
00:45:17,981 --> 00:45:19,501
[SPEAKER_10]: That seems pretty bad.

463
00:45:19,601 --> 00:45:27,643
[SPEAKER_10]: No, but you could put the mechanisms in place to allow it, and if it was offered, you could be okay with that.

464
00:45:28,884 --> 00:45:32,745
[SPEAKER_10]: We don't think we're asking the applicant to commit to that tonight.

465
00:45:34,026 --> 00:45:35,447
[SPEAKER_10]: just to leave that option open.

466
00:45:37,088 --> 00:45:38,569
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you, Director.

467
00:45:38,669 --> 00:45:50,279
[SPEAKER_03]: So just to make my ruling on this clear, so it is not within the board's power to, as a condition of approval, have an applicant donate land.

468
00:45:51,360 --> 00:45:55,043
[SPEAKER_03]: It is within the board's power, if an applicant were to request it,

469
00:45:56,285 --> 00:46:10,293
[SPEAKER_03]: to grant a variance in excess of what's currently on the plans to avoid revisiting the board in the event that a discussion led to that outcome.

470
00:46:10,753 --> 00:46:16,676
[SPEAKER_03]: It's also within the board's power, although I fully acknowledge it leads to some administrative delays,

471
00:46:19,442 --> 00:46:25,344
[SPEAKER_03]: to amend a variance with a visit in a circumstance such as that.

472
00:46:25,464 --> 00:46:33,507
[SPEAKER_03]: So I can't make any assurances as to the outcome, of course, of that revisit, but that is my position on the board's powers here.

473
00:46:36,363 --> 00:46:39,524
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, so I haven't heard a request from the applicant to do that.

474
00:46:40,224 --> 00:46:45,865
[SPEAKER_03]: I'll just double check with you one more time, Attorney Bernowski, and then we'll just resume deliberating.

475
00:46:45,885 --> 00:46:54,647
[SPEAKER_14]: So just so I understand, are you saying that if we request there be dimensional relief granted relative to the carve-out?

476
00:46:54,707 --> 00:46:56,107
[SPEAKER_14]: Is that what we're talking about here?

477
00:46:56,347 --> 00:46:56,587
[SPEAKER_14]: Yes.

478
00:46:57,087 --> 00:46:57,247
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah.

479
00:46:57,367 --> 00:46:59,608
[SPEAKER_14]: And that's the proposal from the planning department.

480
00:47:00,468 --> 00:47:00,588
[SPEAKER_14]: OK.

481
00:47:03,468 --> 00:47:08,293
[SPEAKER_14]: And the only question I have is one, I don't know if the city's attorney is on the line here.

482
00:47:08,313 --> 00:47:16,702
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah, I'm just curious if that, the validity of that, if it hasn't been noticed or gone through those procedures.

483
00:47:19,340 --> 00:47:35,344
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah, I'd wanna make sure that that's a valid grant by the board, but there'd be no objection to that if that's gonna be additional relief that the board has granted that we can work within that without either committing to convey it or to go with easement.

484
00:47:35,664 --> 00:47:37,224
[SPEAKER_14]: I have no objections to that.

485
00:47:37,244 --> 00:47:45,186
[SPEAKER_14]: I would want sign off from the city's council that procedurally that all works, but no objections to it.

486
00:47:45,206 --> 00:47:46,967
[SPEAKER_14]: So if you need me to make the request,

487
00:47:47,547 --> 00:47:51,409
[SPEAKER_14]: we can, although dimensionally, I don't know exactly what we'd be requesting.

488
00:47:52,350 --> 00:47:54,191
[SPEAKER_14]: So I think that that might be a challenge on the fly.

489
00:47:54,671 --> 00:47:55,751
[SPEAKER_03]: Sure, yeah.

490
00:47:56,052 --> 00:48:05,817
[SPEAKER_03]: I tend to agree with your assessment there about the noticing requirements, but let's check in on, do we have a legal representative for the city on?

491
00:48:12,020 --> 00:48:15,402
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay, I know you're not our legal representative, but we can check on that.

492
00:48:17,568 --> 00:48:18,088
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, thank you.

493
00:48:18,368 --> 00:48:35,101
[SPEAKER_01]: I just wanted to say that the legal notice, I believe, just said a modification of the lot area variance that was granted previously, so it didn't specify numerically what it would be.

494
00:48:39,384 --> 00:48:44,108
[SPEAKER_01]: But whatever, so it would be an additional, what, one foot?

495
00:48:45,446 --> 00:48:48,727
[SPEAKER_01]: Or a little over a foot per unit increased.

496
