1243
01:50:19,181 --> 01:50:22,644
[SPEAKER_04]: Needs and how it's affected by the.

1244
01:50:23,805 --> 01:50:26,707
[SPEAKER_04]: By the area that this would be.

1245
01:50:28,028 --> 01:50:30,850
[SPEAKER_04]: Not only an improvement, but it would help for the business as well.

1246
01:50:32,951 --> 01:50:35,173
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you that you're going to say something.

1247
01:50:35,433 --> 01:50:40,137
[SPEAKER_15]: Yeah, I agree with Jamie on their comments.

1248
01:50:42,709 --> 01:50:51,636
[SPEAKER_03]: OK, well, I'm a little torn, so I'll just share my current thought process and kind of where it leads me.

1249
01:50:51,716 --> 01:50:55,679
[SPEAKER_03]: So we are not security experts.

1250
01:50:56,159 --> 01:51:07,828
[SPEAKER_03]: I don't really like that we're being asked to weigh in on something as important as safety and to waive a requirement

1251
01:51:10,076 --> 01:51:14,079
[SPEAKER_03]: in the ordinance that pertains to safety.

1252
01:51:15,560 --> 01:51:17,802
[SPEAKER_03]: I understand this is a complex matter.

1253
01:51:17,882 --> 01:51:29,712
[SPEAKER_03]: We've heard the police chief's letter, and while some of us may not fully agree with the police chief, I certainly respect his position as to why he doesn't feel comfortable approving

1254
01:51:31,633 --> 01:51:32,394
[SPEAKER_03]: things himself.

1255
01:51:32,974 --> 01:51:56,688
[SPEAKER_03]: This does put the board between a rock and a hard place, though, where on the one hand, if we, in the absence of a security expert's independent assessment, refuse to grant this waiver, then the police chief's position could then be a source of potential litigation or something of that nature.

1256
01:51:56,768 --> 01:52:00,191
[SPEAKER_03]: And then on the flip side, if we just grant the

1257
01:52:01,632 --> 01:52:05,895
[SPEAKER_03]: the waiver, you know, we're not security experts.

1258
01:52:05,915 --> 01:52:07,657
[SPEAKER_03]: We're being asked to be security experts.

1259
01:52:07,677 --> 01:52:10,199
[SPEAKER_03]: So I just want to say that out loud.

1260
01:52:10,259 --> 01:52:12,080
[SPEAKER_03]: This is legitimately conflicting.

1261
01:52:14,262 --> 01:52:17,265
[SPEAKER_03]: I think on the other element, it's pretty clear to me.

1262
01:52:17,405 --> 01:52:24,611
[SPEAKER_03]: So just in terms of like the actual statutory interpretation and all that other jazz like that,

1263
01:52:26,966 --> 01:52:36,349
[SPEAKER_03]: the position of the existing fence coupled with this solution and how it essentially requires it to be attached to the existing fence.

1264
01:52:37,610 --> 01:52:48,254
[SPEAKER_03]: And furthermore, the requirement for it to extend above the existing fence to achieve its desired purpose as a alarm system.

1265
